[[File:Bones detail.png|left|120x120px]]
'''Bones''' are the remains of the dead and are dropped by most [[monsters]] with animal or humanoid appearance. Monsters that do not drop bones include [[demons]], [[imp]]s, spirits, [[ghost]]s, [[spider]]s, and insectoids among others. Some monsters drop other [[Remains|specific types of bones]], such as [[big bones]], [[bat bones]], [[monkey bones]] or [[dragon bones]].
[[File:Burying bones.gif|frame|left|A player burying bones.]]

Bones give 4.5 [[Prayer]] experience when buried. This can be increased by offering the bones in different ways: 
* 13.5 XP when casting [[Sinister Offering]].
*13.5 XP when using the [[Sacred Bone Burner]] after the appropriate faith level has been achieved.
* 15.7 XP when offered at a [[gilded altar]] with two burners lit or at the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|Chaos Temple]].
* 18 XP when offered at the [[Ectofuntus]] in the form of [[bonemeal]].

Players may also use the [[Bones to Bananas]] or [[Bones to Peaches]] [[spells]] to turn normal bones to edible [[banana]]s or [[peach]]es.

25 regular bones are used in the [[Demon Slayer]] [[quest]].

